-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Maple, Relapasa, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-24T21:07:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/peru-stocks-buenaventura-maple-relapasa-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.5 percent to 20,637.22. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.4 percent to 2,662.80.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, rose 2.4 percent to 84 centimos after crude rebounded in
New York, said Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based Kallpa
Securities SAB.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, gained 2 percent to $1.03.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper
producer, climbed 1.5 percent to $29.05 after copper advanced in
New York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, rose 2 percent to $38.15 after
gold gained the most in a week in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
